  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Integrated emergency nutrition support for returnees from Mtabila camp through Community-based Management of Acute Malnutrition (CMAM) and emergency infant and young children feeding (e-IYCF) approaches</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">-	30 community health workers and 24 light mothers are active in nutrition screening and referral and nutrition surveillance integrating improved Wash and Infant and Young Children feeding Practices.
-	5 provinces Makamba, Rutana, Ruyigi, Karusi, and Bururi receiving most of returnees with their 11 health districts have set up an early nutrition warning system including nutrition rapid assessments for most affected area hosting returnees using nutrition humanitarian standardized tools.</narrative>
  </description>
